HEADWORD: Conatus
<hw>Co*na"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>conatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>conari</ets> to attempt.]</ety> <def>A
natural tendency inherent in a body to develop itself; an attempt; an
effort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What <qex>conatus</qex> could give prickles to the porcupine or
hedgehog, or to the sheep its fleece?</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concamerate</ent>⟦br⟧
